rting the achievement of the MDGs in Asia-Pacific LDCs. While economic growth does not guarantee poverty reduction in its many dimensions, the presence of growth does make the task easier. The magnitude of development needs in these countries requires a high rate of investment that is not likely to be funded from gross domestic savings alone. In 2003, the resource gap8, meas- ured as the difference", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "5e4c4f05-fefd-4784-9077-79881f2e0332": {"__data__": {"id_": "5e4c4f05-fefd-4784-9077-79881f2e0332", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/voices-least-developed-countries-asia-and-pacific", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Voices of the Least Developed Countries of Asia and the Pacific", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/voices-least-developed-countries-asia-and-pacific", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "2018215985e3de9fd4240a55616e327e172342bb7c679318b782e5ccb1db1d0a"}, "3": {"node_id": "7ed0e4a1-ce31-4ffe-86c4-436c822f4c81", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/voices-least-developed-countries-asia-and-pacific", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "b7d1fffa4cc7173562dd3606e8669b2933c126cdd6093c05a2a5834c1099e11b"}}, "hash": "459f829ceb1dc0b0541476cf95eba51f09fdf8dfb0b231f5d996cedc92b6fa93", "text": "between savings and investment, as a percenta