xt": "65 What role can development partners play in supporting social protection? 66 Final remarks 67 Summary 67 Annex 1: Some guiding principles of real-time social impact monitoring and a possible indicator framework 73 List of Tables Table 1: Pacific Island National Basic Needs Poverty Incidence\u2014Head Count Indices 9 Table 2: Estimated Impact on Level of Poverty Incidence of 10% Real Increase in the Basic Needs Poverty Line in Fiji Islands 10 Table 3: Dependency on imported foods in selected Pacific Island countries 17 Table 4: Food import capacity indicators for selected Pacific Island countries 1990\u20132001 17 Table 5: Maternal Mortality Ratios for 16 Pacific Island countries 26 Table 6: Potential impact of current economic crisis on Pacific Island children and women 32 Table 7: Copenhagen Consensus 2008\u2014best economic investments to solve world challenges 39 Table 8: Selected gender-related indicators in the Pacific Table 9: Different social protection roles and measures Table 10: Advantages and disadvantages of some social protection measures 43 47 52 Table 11: Social Protection Summary Indicators for the Asia-Pacific region Table 12: Social protection across seven key populations (% coverage)\u2014Pacific compared to Asia Table 13: Types of Social Protection in five Pacific Island Countries Table 14: Comparative coverage of social protection for workers in five Pacific Island countries Table 15: Social Protection Index (SPI) for selected Pacific Island countries, Japan, Korea and Asia 55 55 56 57 58 Protecting Pacific Island children and women during economic and", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "962fb923-52c5-4d83-9e02-2f720ca4185a": {"__data__": {"id_": "962fb923-52c5-4d83-9e02-2f720ca4185a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-pacif