ion, tighter credit conditions, etc.) and thus lower spending and investments benefiting children especially nutrition; and second, through more limited access to public services due to tightening government budgets and social spending. We will examine both factors before considering other impacts on children. 2.7. More Pacific Island children will become more malnourished, with long-lasting consequences. Financial crises bring with them severe impacts on the nutrition of children and women (Box 2). Box 2: Financial crisis and children\u2019s nutrition across the globe (UNICEF sources unless cited) \u2022 In rural", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "a2305176-a285-44e4-919c-276b84d9bb05": {"__data__": {"id_": "a2305176-a285-44e4-919c-276b84d9bb05", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-pacific-island-children-women-during-economic-and-food-crises", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Protecting Pacific Island Children & Women during Economic and Food Crises", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-pacific-island-children-women-during-economic-and-food-crises", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "3cf5dc6ec9a6c03d0b5c6b61f6e84eb05f7ff61606aa9da3976b6037a8b1f43b"}, "3": {"node_id": "2f983e2f-975a-4b10-b1c7-c47a40920487", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/protecting-pacific-island-children-women-during-economic-and-food-crises", "Author": "United Nations Deve